                title: 'What Is Resilience?',
        lines: [
          { speaker: 'a', speakerName: 'Maya', en: "Any goal-setting conversation has to include resilience — what to do when things go wrong.", zh: "任何目標設定對話都必須包括韌性——當事情出錯時該怎麼做。", vocab: [{ word: "resilience", def: "韌性；復原力" }] },
          { speaker: 'b', speakerName: 'James', en: "Resilience isn't about never falling — it's about how quickly you get back up.", zh: "韌性不是關於從不跌倒——而是關於你多快爬起來。", vocab: [] },
          { speaker: 'a', speakerName: 'Maya', en: "And what you do with the experience of falling — do you grow from it or are you diminished?", zh: "以及你如何處理跌倒的體驗——你從中成長還是被它削弱？", vocab: [{ word: "diminished", def: "被削弱；被減少" }] },
          { speaker: 'b', speakerName: 'James', en: "The rubber band versus the china metaphor — do you bounce back or shatter?", zh: "橡皮筋對陶瓷的比喻——你彈回來還是碎掉？", vocab: [] },
          { speaker: 'a', speakerName: 'Maya', en: "Resilience can be built — it's not just something you're born with.", zh: "韌性是可以建立的——它不只是你生來就有的東西。", vocab: [] },
          { speaker: 'b', speakerName: 'James', en: "Post-traumatic growth — the evidence that people often emerge stronger from hardship.", zh: "創傷後成長——人們往往從艱辛中更強大地浮現的證據。", vocab: [{ word: "emerge", def: "浮現；出現" }] },
          { speaker: 'a', speakerName: 'Maya', en: "Not everyone does — it requires processing, not just surviving.", zh: "不是每個人都這樣——它需要消化，而不只是生存。", vocab: [{ word: "processing", def: "消化；處理" }] },
          { speaker: 'b', speakerName: 'James', en: "Support, meaning-making, and time are the conditions for growth from difficulty.", zh: "支持、意義建構和時間是從困難中成長的條件。", vocab: [{ word: "meaning-making", def: "意義建構；找到意義" }] },
        ],
